
# Readerfly

#### Overview

ReaderFly is a file monitoring and reporting tool that reads text files in various formats and generates metrics based on their content. It is designed to be flexible and extensible, allowing you to add new file formats and metrics as needed.

## Installation

1) Clone the repository.
2) Build the application using Maven
```bash
mvn clean package
```

3) Run the application using the provided Jar file
```bash
cd target
java -jar readerfly-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar <path/to/monitor>
```

## Usage

To monitor a directory for files to be processed, run the `LocalFileMonitor` class with the directory path as the argument:

```java
Path directory = Paths.get("/path/to/monitor");
ReaderRegister register = RegisterFactory.createRegister();
MetricReporter reporter = ConsoleMetricReporter.withMetrics(
                        new DotCountMetric(),
                        new MostFrequentWordMetric(),
                        new SpecialLetterCountMetric(),
                        new WordCountMetric()
                ));
                
LocalFileMonitor monitor = new LocalFileMonitor(directory, register, reporter);

var service = Executors.newSingleThreadScheduledExecutor();
service.scheduleAtFixedRate(monitor::monitor, 3, 3, TimeUnit.SECONDS);

```
